org.apache.hadoop.thriftfs.jobtracker.api

Class ThriftTaskInProgress

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.hadoop.thriftfs.jobtracker.api.ThriftTaskInProgress
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<ThriftTaskInProgress>, org.apache.thrift.TBase<ThriftTaskInProgress,ThriftTaskInProgress._Fields>

    public class ThriftTaskInProgress
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.apache.thrift.TBase<ThriftTaskInProgress,ThriftTaskInProgress._Fields>, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<ThriftTaskInProgress>
    A ThriftTaskInProgress contains a list of task attempts (speculatively executed instances of the same task). These are indexed by TaskAttemptID. For simplicity, we convert maps keyed on TaskAttemptIDs to maps keyed on their string representation. Assumption: there won't be so many task attempts that retrieving a single task will be too expensive.
